First thing which triggered me to dental clinic is that I started noticing black deposit on my lower jaws, initially I neglected it for a long  time since I didn't experience any bleeding gums or pain or sensitivity and  I thought that it can be removed by brushing ,I  started brushing it regularly and vigorously but no use . Then i searched for dental clinic . Dr Sujatha at Power Smile Dental Clinic examined me carefully and identified that I have periodontitis. She is very experienced in the field and explains each and every step of the treatment in detail. She is friendly enough, you to talk about your dental problems without any hesitation.  Periodontitis is such a serious problems which should be treated before it get worse. After consulting her it was big relief to me to know that I can save my teeth . Treatment went very smoothly at a reasonable cost. Am already seeing the difference and feeling better. Lots of thanks and good wishes to Dr Sujatha.

Dr. Sujatha Pai, is very patient, explains what the problem is and what needs to be done in a layman’s terms. She is very meticulous about the procedures that she follows. She doesn’t prescribe antibiotics unnecessarily. My mother who is 70 years old diabetic had a very bad case of in infection in her gums after dental implants which was neglected by the previous dentist, she educated my mother on how to control her diabetes and why is it important to control it. She also taught my mother how to maintain oral hygiene with her implants. All her inputs has helped us a lot and now my mother is doing really well. Her charges are also very nominal and doesn’t mislead with expensive suggestions. I am really glad that we found her. Thank you! Dr. Sujatha for your dedicated service to my mother.
